  <Name>k__BackingField: Proverbs
  fancyName: 
  nickname: pro
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Beginning of Knowledge'
      title: The Beginning of Knowledge
      number: 1
      content: 'The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: To know wisdom and instruction,To perceive the words of understanding,
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: To receive the instruction of wisdom,Justice, judgment, and equity;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "To give prudence to the simple,To the young man knowledge and discretion\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A wise man will hear and increase learning,And a man of understanding
        will attain wise counsel,
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: To understand a proverb and an enigma,The words of the wise and their
        riddles.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Shun Evil Counsel'
      title: Shun Evil Counsel
      number: 7
      content: The fear of the Lord  is the beginning of knowledge,But fools despise
        wisdom and instruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: My son, hear the instruction of your father,And do not forsake the
        law of your mother;
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For they will  be a graceful ornament on your head,And chains about
        your neck.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: My son, if sinners entice you,Do not consent.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If they say, \u201CCome with us,Let us lie in wait to shed blood;Let
        us lurk secretly for the innocent without cause;"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Let us swallow them alive like Sheol,And whole, like those who go
        down to the Pit;
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: We shall find all kinds of precious possessions,We shall fill our
        houses with spoil;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Cast in your lot among us,Let us all have one purse\u201D\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: My son, do not walk in the way with them,Keep your foot from their
        path;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For their feet run to evil,And they make haste to shed blood.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Surely, in vain the net is spreadIn the sight of any bird;
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But they lie in wait for their own blood,They lurk secretly for their
        own lives.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Call of Wisdom'
      title: The Call of Wisdom
      number: 19
      content: So are the ways of everyone who is greedy for gain;It takes away the
        life of its owners.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Wisdom calls aloud outside;She raises her voice in the open squares.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'She cries out in the chief concourses,At the openings of the gates
        in the cityShe speaks her words:'
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CHow long, you simple ones, will you love simplicity?For scorners
        delight in their scorning,And fools hate knowledge."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Turn at my rebuke;Surely I will pour out my spirit on you;I will make
        my words known to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Because I have called and you refused,I have stretched out my hand
        and no one regarded,
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Because you disdained all my counsel,And would have none of my rebuke,
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: I also will laugh at your calamity;I will mock when your terror comes,
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: When your terror comes like a storm,And your destruction comes like
        a whirlwind,When distress and anguish come upon you.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CThen they will call on me, but I will not answer;They will
        seek me diligently, but they will not find me."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Because they hated knowledgeAnd did not choose the fear of the Lord,
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: They would have none of my counselAnd despised my every rebuke.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Therefore they shall eat the fruit of their own way,And be filled
        to the full with their own fancies.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: For the turning away of the simple will slay them,And the complacency
        of fools will destroy them;
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But whoever listens to me will dwell safely,And will be secure, without
        fear of evil.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Value of Wisdom'
      title: The Value of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: My son, if you receive my words,And treasure my commands within you,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: So that you incline your ear to wisdom,And apply your heart to understanding;
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Yes, if you cry out for discernment,And lift up your voice for understanding,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: If you seek her as silver,And search for her as for hidden treasures;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Then you will understand the fear of the Lord,And find the knowledge
        of God.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For the Lord gives wisdom;From His mouth come knowledge and understanding;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: He stores up sound wisdom for the upright;He  is a shield to those
        who walk uprightly;
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He guards the paths of justice,And preserves the way of His saints.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then you will understand righteousness and justice,Equity and every
        good path.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When wisdom enters your heart,And knowledge is pleasant to your soul,
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Discretion will preserve you;Understanding will keep you,
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: To deliver you from the way of evil,From the man who speaks perverse
        things,
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: From those who leave the paths of uprightnessTo walk in the ways of
        darkness;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Who rejoice in doing evil,And delight in the perversity of the wicked;
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Whose ways are crooked,And who  are devious in their paths;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: To deliver you from the immoral woman,From the seductress who flatters
        with her words,
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Who forsakes the companion of her youth,And forgets the covenant of
        her God.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For her house leads down to death,And her paths to the dead;
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "None who go to her return,Nor do they regain the paths of life\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So you may walk in the way of goodness,And keep to the paths of righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For the upright will dwell in the land,And the blameless will remain
        in it;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: But the wicked will be cut off from the earth,And the unfaithful will
        be uprooted from it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Guidance for the Young'
      title: Guidance for the Young
      number: 1
      content: My son, do not forget my law,But let your heart keep my commands;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For length of days and long lifeAnd peace they will add to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Let not mercy and truth forsake you;Bind them around your neck,Write
        them on the tablet of your heart,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And so find favor and high esteemIn the sight of God and man.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Trust in the Lord with all your heart,And lean not on your own understanding;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: In all your ways acknowledge Him,And He shall direct your paths.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Do not be wise in your own eyes;Fear the Lord and depart from evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: It will be health to your flesh,And strength to your bones.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Honor the Lord with your possessions,And with the firstfruits of all
        your increase;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So your barns will be filled with plenty,And your vats will overflow
        with new wine.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: My son, do not despise the chastening of the Lord,Nor detest His correction;
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: For whom the Lord loves He corrects,Just as a father the son in  whom
        he delights.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Happy is the man who finds wisdom,And the man who gains understanding;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For her proceeds are better than the profits of silver,And her gain
        than fine gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: She is more precious than rubies,And all the things you may desire
        cannot compare with her.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Length of days is in her right hand,In her left hand riches and honor.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Her ways are ways of pleasantness,And all her paths are peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: She is  a tree of life to those who take hold of her,And happy are 
        all who retain her.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The Lord by wisdom founded the earth;By understanding He established
        the heavens;
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: By His knowledge the depths were broken up,And clouds drop down the
        dew.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "My son, let them not depart from your eyes\u2014Keep sound wisdom
        and discretion;"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So they will be life to your soulAnd grace to your neck.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Then you will walk safely in your way,And your foot will not stumble.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: When you lie down, you will not be afraid;Yes, you will lie down and
        your sleep will be sweet.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Do not be afraid of sudden terror,Nor of trouble from the wicked when
        it comes;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For the Lord will be your confidence,And will keep your foot from
        being caught.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Do not withhold good from those to whom it is due,When it is in the
        power of your hand to do so.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do not say to your neighbor,\u201CGo, and come back,And tomorrow
        I will give it,\u201DWhen you have it with you."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Do not devise evil against your neighbor,For he dwells by you for
        safety\u2019s sake."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Do not strive with a man without cause,If he has done you no harm.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Do not envy the oppressor,And choose none of his ways;
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: For the perverse person  is an abomination to the Lord,But His secret
        counsel is with the upright.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: The curse of the Lord  is on the house of the wicked,But He blesses
        the home of the just.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Surely He scorns the scornful,But gives grace to the humble.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: The wise shall inherit glory,But shame shall be the legacy of fools.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Security in Wisdom'
      title: Security in Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: Hear, my children, the instruction of a father,And give attention
        to know understanding;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For I give you good doctrine:Do not forsake my law.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When I was my father\u2019s son,Tender and the only one in the sight
        of my mother,"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He also taught me, and said to me:\u201CLet your heart retain my
        words;Keep my commands, and live."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Get wisdom! Get understanding!Do not forget, nor turn away from the
        words of my mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Do not forsake her, and she will preserve you;Love her, and she will
        keep you.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Wisdom is the principal thing;Therefore get wisdom.And in all your
        getting, get understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Exalt her, and she will promote you;She will bring you honor, when
        you embrace her.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She will place on your head an ornament of grace;A crown of glory
        she will deliver to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Hear, my son, and receive my sayings,And the years of your life will
        be many.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: I have taught you in the way of wisdom;I have led you in right paths.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: When you walk, your steps will not be hindered,And when you run, you
        will not stumble.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Take firm hold of instruction, do not let go;Keep her, for she is
        your life.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Do not enter the path of the wicked,And do not walk in the way of
        evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Avoid it, do not travel on it;Turn away from it and pass on.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For they do not sleep unless they have done evil;And their sleep is
        taken away unless they make someone fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: For they eat the bread of wickedness,And drink the wine of violence.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But the path of the just is like the shining sun,That shines ever
        brighter unto the perfect day.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The way of the wicked is like darkness;They do not know what makes
        them stumble.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: My son, give attention to my words;Incline your ear to my sayings.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Do not let them depart from your eyes;Keep them in the midst of your
        heart;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For they are life to those who find them,And health to all their flesh.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Keep your heart with all diligence,For out of it spring the issues
        of life.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Put away from you a deceitful mouth,And put perverse lips far from
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Let your eyes look straight ahead,And your eyelids look right before
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Ponder the path of your feet,And let all your ways be established.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Do not turn to the right or the left;Remove your foot from evil.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Peril of Adultery'
      title: The Peril of Adultery
      number: 1
      content: My son, pay attention to my wisdom;Lend your ear to my understanding,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: That you may preserve discretion,And your lips may keep knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: For the lips of an immoral woman drip honey,And her mouth is  smoother
        than oil;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: But in the end she is bitter as wormwood,Sharp as a two-edged sword.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Her feet go down to death,Her steps lay hold of hell.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Lest you ponder her path of life\u2014Her ways are unstable;You do
        not know them."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Therefore hear me now, my children,And do not depart from the words
        of my mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Remove your way far from her,And do not go near the door of her house,
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Lest you give your honor to others,And your years to the cruel one;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Lest aliens be filled with your wealth,And your labors go to the house
        of a foreigner;
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: And you mourn at last,When your flesh and your body are consumed,
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And say:\u201CHow I have hated instruction,And my heart despised
        correction!"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: I have not obeyed the voice of my teachers,Nor inclined my ear to
        those who instructed me!
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I was on the verge of total ruin,In the midst of the assembly and
        congregation.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Drink water from your own cistern,And running water from your own
        well.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Should your fountains be dispersed abroad,Streams of water in the
        streets?
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Let them be only your own,And not for strangers with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Let your fountain be blessed,And rejoice with the wife of your youth.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: As  a loving deer and a graceful doe,Let her breasts satisfy you at
        all times;And always be enraptured with her love.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: For why should you, my son, be enraptured by an immoral woman,And
        be embraced in the arms of a seductress?
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For the ways of man are before the eyes of the Lord,And He ponders
        all his paths.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: His own iniquities entrap the wicked man,And he is caught in the cords
        of his sin.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He shall die for lack of instruction,And in the greatness of his folly
        he shall go astray.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Dangerous Promises'
      title: Dangerous Promises
      number: 1
      content: My son, if you become surety for your friend,If you have shaken hands
        in pledge for a stranger,
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: You are snared by the words of your mouth;You are taken by the words
        of your mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: So do this, my son, and deliver yourself;For you have come into the
        hand of your friend:Go and humble yourself;Plead with your friend.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Give no sleep to your eyes,Nor slumber to your eyelids.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Folly of Indolence'
      title: The Folly of Indolence
      number: 5
      content: Deliver yourself like a gazelle from the hand of  the  hunter,And
        like a bird from the hand of the fowler.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Go to the ant, you sluggard!Consider her ways and be wise,
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Which, having no captain,Overseer or ruler,
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Provides her supplies in the summer,And gathers her food in the harvest.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: How long will you slumber, O sluggard?When will you rise from your
        sleep?
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "A little sleep, a little slumber,A little folding of the hands to
        sleep\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Wicked Man'
      title: The Wicked Man
      number: 11
      content: So shall your poverty come on you like a prowler,And your need like
        an armed man.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: A worthless person, a wicked man,Walks with a perverse mouth;
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He winks with his eyes,He shuffles his feet,He points with his fingers;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Perversity is in his heart,He devises evil continually,He sows discord.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Therefore his calamity shall come suddenly;Suddenly he shall be broken
        without remedy.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These six things the Lord hates,Yes, seven are an abomination to
        Him:'
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: A proud look,A lying tongue,Hands that shed innocent blood,
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: A heart that devises wicked plans,Feet that are swift in running to
        evil,
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Beware of Adultery'
      title: Beware of Adultery
      number: 19
      content: A false witness who speaks lies,And one who sows discord among brethren.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "My son, keep your father\u2019s command,And do not forsake the law
        of your mother."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Bind them continually upon your heart;Tie them around your neck.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: When you roam, they will lead you;When you sleep, they will keep you;And
        when you awake, they will speak with you.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For the commandment is a lamp,And the law a light;Reproofs of instruction
        are the way of life,
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: To keep you from the evil woman,From the flattering tongue of a seductress.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Do not lust after her beauty in your heart,Nor let her allure you
        with her eyelids.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For by means of a harlotA  man  is  reduced to a crust of bread;And
        an adulteress will prey upon his precious life.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Can a man take fire to his bosom,And his clothes not be burned?
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Can one walk on hot coals,And his feet not be seared?
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So is he who goes in to his neighbor\u2019s wife;Whoever touches
        her shall not be innocent."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: People do not despise a thiefIf he steals to satisfy himself when
        he is starving.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Yet when he is found, he must restore sevenfold;He may have to give
        up all the substance of his house.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: Whoever commits adultery with a woman lacks understanding;He who does
        so destroys his own soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Wounds and dishonor he will get,And his reproach will not be wiped
        away.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "For jealousy is a husband\u2019s fury;Therefore he will not spare
        in the day of vengeance."
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: He will accept no recompense,Nor will he be appeased though you give
        many gifts.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: My son, keep my words,And treasure my commands within you.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Keep my commands and live,And my law as the apple of your eye.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Bind them on your fingers;Write them on the tablet of your heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to wisdom, \u201CYou are my sister,\u201DAnd call understanding
        your nearest kin,"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: The Crafty Harlot'
      title: The Crafty Harlot
      number: 5
      content: That they may keep you from the immoral woman,From the seductress
        who flatters with her words.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For at the window of my houseI looked through my lattice,
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: And saw among the simple,I perceived among the youths,A young man
        devoid of understanding,
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Passing along the street near her corner;And he took the path to her
        house
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: In the twilight, in the evening,In the black and dark night.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And there a woman met him,With the attire of a harlot, and a crafty
        heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: She was loud and rebellious,Her feet would not stay at home.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: At times she  was outside, at times in the open square,Lurking at
        every corner.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So she caught him and kissed him;With an impudent face she said to
        him:'
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI  have peace offerings with me;Today I have paid my vows."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So I came out to meet you,Diligently to seek your face,And I have
        found you.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I have spread my bed with tapestry,Colored coverings of Egyptian linen.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I have perfumed my bedWith myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Come, let us take our fill of love until morning;Let us delight ourselves
        with love.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: For my husband is not at home;He has gone on a long journey;
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He has taken a bag of money with him,And will come home on the appointed
        day.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: With her enticing speech she caused him to yield,With her flattering
        lips she seduced him.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Immediately he went after her, as an ox goes to the slaughter,Or as
        a fool to the correction of the stocks,
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Till an arrow struck his liver.As a bird hastens to the snare,He did
        not know it would  cost his life.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now therefore, listen to me, my children;Pay attention to the words
        of my mouth:'
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways,Do not stray into her
        paths;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: For she has cast down many wounded,And all who were slain by her were
        strong men.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Her house is the way to hell,Descending to the chambers of death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Excellence of Wisdom'
      title: The Excellence of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: Does not wisdom cry out,And understanding lift up her voice?
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: She takes her stand on the top of the high hill,Beside the way, where
        the paths meet.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'She cries out by the gates, at the entry of the city,At the entrance
        of the doors:'
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTo you, O men, I call,And my voice is to the sons of men."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: O you simple ones, understand prudence,And you fools, be of an understanding
        heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Listen, for I will speak of excellent things,And from the opening
        of my lips will  come right things;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For my mouth will speak truth;Wickedness is an abomination to my lips.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: All the words of my mouth are with righteousness;Nothing crooked or
        perverse is in them.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: They are all plain to him who understands,And right to those who find
        knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Receive my instruction, and not silver,And knowledge rather than choice
        gold;
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For wisdom is better than rubies,And all the things one may desire
        cannot be compared with her.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI, wisdom, dwell with prudence,And find out knowledge and discretion."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The fear of the Lord  is to hate evil;Pride and arrogance and the
        evil wayAnd the perverse mouth I hate.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Counsel is mine, and sound wisdom;I am understanding, I have strength.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: By me kings reign,And rulers decree justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: By me princes rule, and nobles,All the judges of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: I love those who love me,And those who seek me diligently will find
        me.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Riches and honor are with me,Enduring riches and righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: My fruit is better than gold, yes, than fine gold,And my revenue than
        choice silver.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: I traverse the way of righteousness,In the midst of the paths of justice,
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: That I may cause those who love me to inherit wealth,That I may fill
        their treasuries.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThe  Lord possessed me at the beginning of His way,Before His
        works of old."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: I have been established from everlasting,From the beginning, before
        there was ever an earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: When there  were no depths I was brought forth,When there  were no
        fountains abounding with water.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Before the mountains were settled,Before the hills, I was brought
        forth;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: While as yet He had not made the earth or the fields,Or the primal
        dust of the world.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: When He prepared the heavens, I was there,When He drew a circle on
        the face of the deep,
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: When He established the clouds above,When He strengthened the fountains
        of the deep,
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: When He assigned to the sea its limit,So that the waters would not
        transgress His command,When He marked out the foundations of the earth,
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Then I was beside Him as a master craftsman;And I was daily His delight,Rejoicing
        always before Him,
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Rejoicing in His inhabited world,And my delight was with the sons
        of men.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, listen to me, my children,For blessed are  those 
        who keep my ways."
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Hear instruction and be wise,And do not disdain it.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Blessed is the man who listens to me,Watching daily at my gates,Waiting
        at the posts of my doors.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: For whoever finds me finds life,And obtains favor from the Lord;
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But he who sins against me wrongs his own soul;All those who hate
        me love death.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Way of Wisdom'
      title: The Way of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: Wisdom has built her house,She has hewn out her seven pillars;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: She has slaughtered her meat,She has mixed her wine,She has also furnished
        her table.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: She has sent out her maidens,She cries out from the highest places
        of the city,
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhoever  is simple, let him turn in here!\u201DAs  for him
        who lacks understanding, she says to him,"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CCome, eat of my breadAnd drink of the wine I have mixed."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Forsake foolishness and live,And go in the way of understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CHe who corrects a scoffer gets shame for himself,And he who
        rebukes a wicked man  only harms himself."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Do not correct a scoffer, lest he hate you;Rebuke a wise man, and
        he will love you.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Give instruction to a wise man, and he will be still wiser;Teach a
        just man,  and he will increase in learning.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe fear of the Lord  is the beginning of wisdom,And the knowledge
        of the Holy One is understanding."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For by me your days will be multiplied,And years of life will be added
        to you.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Way of Folly'
      title: The Way of Folly
      number: 12
      content: "If you are wise, you are wise for yourself,And if you scoff, you
        will bear it alone.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: A foolish woman is clamorous;She  is simple, and knows nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For she sits at the door of her house,On a seat by the highest places
        of the city,
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'To call to those who pass by,Who go straight on their way:'
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWhoever  is simple, let him turn in here\u201D;And as  for
        him who lacks understanding, she says to him,"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CStolen water is sweet,And bread eaten in secret is pleasant.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But he does not know that the dead are there,That her guests are in
        the depths of hell.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wise Sayings of Solomon'
      title: Wise Sayings of Solomon
      number: 1
      content: The proverbs of Solomon:A wise son makes a glad father,But a foolish
        son is the grief of his mother.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Treasures of wickedness profit nothing,But righteousness delivers
        from death.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The Lord will not allow the righteous soul to famish,But He casts
        away the desire of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: He who has a slack hand becomes poor,But the hand of the diligent
        makes rich.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He who gathers in summer is a wise son;He who sleeps in harvest is 
        a son who causes shame.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Blessings are on the head of the righteous,But violence covers the
        mouth of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The memory of the righteous is blessed,But the name of the wicked
        will rot.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The wise in heart will receive commands,But a prating fool will fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He who walks with integrity walks securely,But he who perverts his
        ways will become known.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He who winks with the eye causes trouble,But a prating fool will fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The mouth of the righteous is a well of life,But violence covers the
        mouth of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Hatred stirs up strife,But love covers all sins.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Wisdom is found on the lips of him who has understanding,But a rod
        is for the back of him who is devoid of understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Wise people store up knowledge,But the mouth of the foolish is near
        destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The rich man\u2019s wealth is his strong city;The destruction of
        the poor is their poverty."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The labor of the righteous leads to life,The wages of the wicked to
        sin.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He who keeps instruction is  in the way of life,But he who refuses
        correction goes astray.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Whoever hides hatred has lying lips,And whoever spreads slander is
        a fool.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: In the multitude of words sin is not lacking,But he who restrains
        his lips is wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The tongue of the righteous is choice silver;The heart of the wicked
        is  worth little.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The lips of the righteous feed many,But fools die for lack of wisdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The blessing of the Lord makes one rich,And He adds no sorrow with
        it.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: To do evil is like sport to a fool,But a man of understanding has
        wisdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The fear of the wicked will come upon him,And the desire of the righteous
        will be granted.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: When the whirlwind passes by, the wicked is no more,But the righteous
        has an everlasting foundation.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: As vinegar to the teeth and smoke to the eyes,So is the lazy man to
        those who send him.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The fear of the Lord prolongs days,But the years of the wicked will
        be shortened.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The hope of the righteous will  be gladness,But the expectation of
        the wicked will perish.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The way of the Lord  is strength for the upright,But destruction will 
        come to the workers of iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The righteous will never be removed,But the wicked will not inhabit
        the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The mouth of the righteous brings forth wisdom,But the perverse tongue
        will be cut out.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable,But the mouth of
        the wicked what  is perverse.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Dishonest scales are an abomination to the Lord,But a just weight
        is His delight.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: When pride comes, then comes shame;But with the humble is wisdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The integrity of the upright will guide them,But the perversity of
        the unfaithful will destroy them.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Riches do not profit in the day of wrath,But righteousness delivers
        from death.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The righteousness of the blameless will direct his way aright,But
        the wicked will fall by his own wickedness.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: The righteousness of the upright will deliver them,But the unfaithful
        will be caught by their lust.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: When a wicked man dies, his expectation will perish,And the hope of
        the unjust perishes.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The righteous is delivered from trouble,And it comes to the wicked
        instead.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The hypocrite with his mouth destroys his neighbor,But through knowledge
        the righteous will be delivered.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices;And when the
        wicked perish, there  is jubilation.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted,But it is overthrown
        by the mouth of the wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: He who is devoid of wisdom despises his neighbor,But a man of understanding
        holds his peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: A talebearer reveals secrets,But he who is of a faithful spirit conceals
        a matter.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Where there  is no counsel, the people fall;But in the multitude of
        counselors there  is safety.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He who is surety for a stranger will suffer,But one who hates being
        surety is secure.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: A gracious woman retains honor,But ruthless men retain riches.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The merciful man does good for his own soul,But he  who  is cruel
        troubles his own flesh.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The wicked man does deceptive work,But he who sows righteousness will 
        have a sure reward.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: As righteousness leads to life,So he who pursues evil pursues  it
        to his own death.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Those who are of a perverse heart are an abomination to the Lord,But
        the blameless in their ways are His delight.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Though they join forces, the wicked will not go unpunished;But the
        posterity of the righteous will be delivered.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As a ring of gold in a swine\u2019s snout,So  is a lovely woman who
        lacks discretion."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The desire of the righteous is only good,But the expectation of the
        wicked is wrath.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: There is one who scatters, yet increases more;And there is one who
        withholds more than is right,But it leads to poverty.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The generous soul will be made rich,And he who waters will also be
        watered himself.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The people will curse him who withholds grain,But blessing will  be
        on the head of him who sells it.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: He who earnestly seeks good finds favor,But trouble will come to him
        who seeks evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: He who trusts in his riches will fall,But the righteous will flourish
        like foliage.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: He who troubles his own house will inherit the wind,And the fool will 
        be  servant to the wise of heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The fruit of the righteous is  a tree of life,And he who wins souls
        is wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: If the righteous will be recompensed on the earth,How much more the
        ungodly and the sinner.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Whoever loves instruction loves knowledge,But he who hates correction
        is stupid.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: A good man obtains favor from the Lord,But a man of wicked intentions
        He will condemn.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: A man is not established by wickedness,But the root of the righteous
        cannot be moved.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: An excellent wife is the crown of her husband,But she who causes shame
        is  like rottenness in his bones.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The thoughts of the righteous are right,But the counsels of the wicked
        are deceitful.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The words of the wicked are, \u201CLie in wait for blood,\u201DBut
        the mouth of the upright will deliver them."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The wicked are overthrown and are no more,But the house of the righteous
        will stand.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: A man will be commended according to his wisdom,But he who is of a
        perverse heart will be despised.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Better is  the  one who is slighted but has a servant,Than he who
        honors himself but lacks bread.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: A righteous man regards the life of his animal,But the tender mercies
        of the wicked are cruel.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He who tills his land will be satisfied with bread,But he who follows
        frivolity is devoid of understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The wicked covet the catch of evil men,But the root of the righteous
        yields fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The wicked is ensnared by the transgression of his lips,But the righteous
        will come through trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "A man will be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth,And the
        recompense of a man\u2019s hands will be rendered to him."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The way of a fool is right in his own eyes,But he who heeds counsel
        is wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "A fool\u2019s wrath is known at once,But a prudent man covers shame."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He who speaks truth declares righteousness,But a false witness, deceit.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: There is one who speaks like the piercings of a sword,But the tongue
        of the wise promotes health.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The truthful lip shall be established forever,But a lying tongue is
        but for a moment.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Deceit is in the heart of those who devise evil,But counselors of
        peace have joy.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: No grave trouble will overtake the righteous,But the wicked shall
        be filled with evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Lying lips are an abomination to the Lord,But those who deal truthfully
        are His delight.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: A prudent man conceals knowledge,But the heart of fools proclaims
        foolishness.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The hand of the diligent will rule,But the lazy man will be put to
        forced labor.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Anxiety in the heart of man causes depression,But a good word makes
        it glad.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The righteous should choose his friends carefully,For the way of the
        wicked leads them astray.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The lazy man does not roast what he took in hunting,But diligence
        is man\u2019s precious possession."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: In the way of righteousness is life,And in its pathway there  is no
        death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "A wise son heeds his father\u2019s instruction,But a scoffer does
        not listen to rebuke."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: A man shall eat well by the fruit of his mouth,But the soul of the
        unfaithful feeds on violence.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: He who guards his mouth preserves his life,But he who opens wide his
        lips shall have destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The soul of a lazy man desires, and has nothing;But the soul of the
        diligent shall be made rich.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A righteous man hates lying,But a wicked man is loathsome and comes
        to shame.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Righteousness guards him  whose way is blameless,But wickedness overthrows
        the sinner.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: There is one who makes himself rich, yet has nothing;And one who makes
        himself poor, yet has great riches.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The ransom of a man\u2019s life is his riches,But the poor does not
        hear rebuke."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The light of the righteous rejoices,But the lamp of the wicked will
        be put out.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: By pride comes nothing but strife,But with the well-advised is wisdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Wealth gained  by dishonesty will be diminished,But he who gathers
        by labor will increase.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Hope deferred makes the heart sick,But when the desire comes, it 
        is a tree of life.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He who despises the word will be destroyed,But he who fears the commandment
        will be rewarded.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The law of the wise is a fountain of life,To turn one away from the
        snares of death.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Good understanding gains favor,But the way of the unfaithful is hard.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Every prudent man acts with knowledge,But a fool lays open his folly.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: A wicked messenger falls into trouble,But a faithful ambassador brings
        health.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Poverty and shame will  come to him who disdains correction,But he
        who regards a rebuke will be honored.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: A desire accomplished is sweet to the soul,But it  is an abomination
        to fools to depart from evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He who walks with wise men will be wise,But the companion of fools
        will be destroyed.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Evil pursues sinners,But to the righteous, good shall be repaid.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A good man leaves an inheritance to his children\u2019s children,But
        the wealth of the sinner is stored up for the righteous."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Much food is  in the fallow ground of the poor,And for lack of justice
        there is waste.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He who spares his rod hates his son,But he who loves him disciplines
        him promptly.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The righteous eats to the satisfying of his soul,But the stomach of
        the wicked shall be in want.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: The wise woman builds her house,But the foolish pulls it down with
        her hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He who walks in his uprightness fears the Lord,But he  who  is perverse
        in his ways despises Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: In the mouth of a fool is a rod of pride,But the lips of the wise
        will preserve them.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Where no oxen are, the trough is clean;But much increase comes by
        the strength of an ox.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A faithful witness does not lie,But a false witness will utter lies.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: A scoffer seeks wisdom and does not find  it,But knowledge is easy
        to him who understands.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Go from the presence of a foolish man,When you do not perceive in 
        him the lips of knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The wisdom of the prudent is to understand his way,But the folly of
        fools is deceit.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Fools mock at sin,But among the upright there  is favor.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The heart knows its own bitterness,And a stranger does not share its
        joy.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The house of the wicked will be overthrown,But the tent of the upright
        will flourish.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: There is a way that  seems right to a man,But its end is the way of
        death.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Even in laughter the heart may sorrow,And the end of mirth may  be
        grief.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The backslider in heart will be filled with his own ways,But a good
        man will  be  satisfied from above.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The simple believes every word,But the prudent considers well his
        steps.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: A wise man fears and departs from evil,But a fool rages and is self-confident.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: A quick-tempered man acts foolishly,And a man of wicked intentions
        is hated.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The simple inherit folly,But the prudent are crowned with knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The evil will bow before the good,And the wicked at the gates of the
        righteous.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The poor man is hated even by his own neighbor,But the rich has many
        friends.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He who despises his neighbor sins;But he who has mercy on the poor,
        happy is he.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Do they not go astray who devise evil?But mercy and truth belong to
        those who devise good.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: In all labor there is profit,But idle chatter leads only to poverty.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The crown of the wise is their riches,But the foolishness of fools
        is folly.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: A true witness delivers souls,But a deceitful witness speaks lies.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: In the fear of the Lord  there  is strong confidence,And His children
        will have a place of refuge.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The fear of the Lord  is a fountain of life,To turn one away from
        the snares of death.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "In a multitude of people is a king\u2019s honor,But in the lack of
        people is the downfall of a prince."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: He  who  is slow to wrath has great understanding,But he  who  is
        impulsive exalts folly.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: A sound heart is life to the body,But envy is  rottenness to the bones.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: He who oppresses the poor reproaches his Maker,But he who honors Him
        has mercy on the needy.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The wicked is banished in his wickedness,But the righteous has a refuge
        in his death.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Wisdom rests in the heart of him who has understanding,But what  is
        in the heart of fools is made known.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Righteousness exalts a nation,But sin is a reproach to any people.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "The king\u2019s favor is toward a wise servant,But his wrath is 
        against him who causes shame."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: A soft answer turns away wrath,But a harsh word stirs up anger.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The tongue of the wise uses knowledge rightly,But the mouth of fools
        pours forth foolishness.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The eyes of the Lord  are in every place,Keeping watch on the evil
        and the good.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: A wholesome tongue is a tree of life,But perverseness in it breaks
        the spirit.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "A fool despises his father\u2019s instruction,But he who receives
        correction is prudent."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: In the house of the righteous there  is much treasure,But in the revenue
        of the wicked is trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The lips of the wise disperse knowledge,But the heart of the fool
        does not do so.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to the Lord,But the
        prayer of the upright is His delight.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The way of the wicked is an abomination to the Lord,But He loves him
        who follows righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Harsh discipline is for him who forsakes the way,And  he who hates
        correction will die.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Hell and Destruction are before the Lord;So how much more the hearts
        of the sons of men.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: A scoffer does not love one who corrects him,Nor will he go to the
        wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: A merry heart makes a cheerful countenance,But by sorrow of the heart
        the spirit is broken.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The heart of him who has understanding seeks knowledge,But the mouth
        of fools feeds on foolishness.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: All the days of the afflicted are evil,But he who is of a merry heart
        has a continual feast.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Better is a little with the fear of the Lord,Than great treasure with
        trouble.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Better is a dinner of herbs where love is,Than a fatted calf with
        hatred.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: A wrathful man stirs up strife,But he  who  is slow to anger allays
        contention.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The way of the lazy man  is like a hedge of thorns,But the way of
        the upright is a highway.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: A wise son makes a father glad,But a foolish man despises his mother.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Folly is joy to  him  who  is destitute of discernment,But a man of
        understanding walks uprightly.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Without counsel, plans go awry,But in the multitude of counselors
        they are established.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: A man has joy by the answer of his mouth,And a word spoken in due
        season, how good it  is!
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The way of life winds upward for the wise,That he may turn away from
        hell below.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The Lord will destroy the house of the proud,But He will establish
        the boundary of the widow.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the Lord,But the
        words of the pure are pleasant.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: He who is greedy for gain troubles his own house,But he who hates
        bribes will live.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: The heart of the righteous studies how to answer,But the mouth of
        the wicked pours forth evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The Lord  is far from the wicked,But He hears the prayer of the righteous.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: The light of the eyes rejoices the heart,And a good report makes the
        bones healthy.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The ear that hears the rebukes of lifeWill abide among the wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: He who disdains instruction despises his own soul,But he who heeds
        rebuke gets understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: The fear of the Lord  is the instruction of wisdom,And before honor
        is humility.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: The preparations of the heart belong to man,But the answer of the
        tongue is from the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: All the ways of a man are pure in his own eyes,But the Lord weighs
        the spirits.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Commit your works to the Lord,And your thoughts will be established.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The Lord has made all for Himself,Yes, even the wicked for the day
        of doom.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Everyone proud in heart is an abomination to the Lord;Though  they 
        join forces, none will go unpunished.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: In mercy and truthAtonement is provided for iniquity;And by the fear
        of the Lord  one departs from evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When a man\u2019s ways please the Lord,He makes even his enemies
        to be at peace with him."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Better is a little with righteousness,Than vast revenues without justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "A man\u2019s heart plans his way,But the Lord directs his steps."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Divination is on the lips of the king;His mouth must not transgress
        in judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Honest weights and scales are the Lord\u2019s;All the weights in
        the bag are His work."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: It  is an abomination for kings to commit wickedness,For a throne
        is established by righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Righteous lips are the delight of kings,And they love him who speaks
        what  is right.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "As messengers of death is the king\u2019s wrath,But a wise man will
        appease it."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "In the light of the king\u2019s face is life,And his favor is like
        a cloud of the latter rain."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: How much better to get wisdom than gold!And to get understanding is
        to be chosen rather than silver.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The highway of the upright is to depart from evil;He who keeps his
        way preserves his soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Pride goes before destruction,And a haughty spirit before a fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Better to  be of a humble spirit with the lowly,Than to divide the
        spoil with the proud.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He who heeds the word wisely will find good,And whoever trusts in
        the Lord, happy is he.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The wise in heart will be called prudent,And sweetness of the lips
        increases learning.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Understanding is a wellspring of life to him who has it.But the correction
        of fools is folly.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The heart of the wise teaches his mouth,And adds learning to his lips.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Pleasant words are  like a honeycomb,Sweetness to the soul and health
        to the bones.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: There is a way that  seems right to a man,But its end is the way of
        death.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The person who labors, labors for himself,For his hungry mouth drives
        him on.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: An ungodly man digs up evil,And it  is on his lips like a burning
        fire.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A perverse man sows strife,And a whisperer separates the best of friends.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: A violent man entices his neighbor,And leads him in a way that  is
        not good.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: He winks his eye to devise perverse things;He purses his lips and
        brings about evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The silver-haired head is a crown of glory,If it is found in the way
        of righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: He  who  is slow to anger is better than the mighty,And he who rules
        his spirit than he who takes a city.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: The lot is cast into the lap,But its every decision is from the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Better is  a dry morsel with quietness,Than a house full of feasting
        with strife.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: A wise servant will rule over a son who causes shame,And will share
        an inheritance among the brothers.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The refining pot is for silver and the furnace for gold,But the Lord
        tests the hearts.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: An evildoer gives heed to false lips;A liar listens eagerly to a spiteful
        tongue.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He who mocks the poor reproaches his Maker;He who is glad at calamity
        will not go unpunished.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Children\u2019s children are the crown of old men,And the glory of
        children is their father."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Excellent speech is not becoming to a fool,Much less lying lips to
        a prince.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: A present is a precious stone in the eyes of its possessor;Wherever
        he turns, he prospers.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He who covers a transgression seeks love,But he who repeats a matter
        separates friends.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Rebuke is more effective for a wise manThan a hundred blows on a fool.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: An evil man seeks only rebellion;Therefore a cruel messenger will
        be sent against him.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Let a man meet a bear robbed of her cubs,Rather than a fool in his
        folly.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Whoever rewards evil for good,Evil will not depart from his house.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The beginning of strife is  like releasing water;Therefore stop contention
        before a quarrel starts.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: He who justifies the wicked, and he who condemns the just,Both of
        them alike are an abomination to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Why is  there in the hand of a fool the purchase price of wisdom,Since
        he  has no heart for  it?
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: A friend loves at all times,And a brother is born for adversity.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: A man devoid of understanding shakes hands in a pledge,And becomes
        surety for his friend.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He who loves transgression loves strife,And he who exalts his gate
        seeks destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: He who has a deceitful heart finds no good,And he who has a perverse
        tongue falls into evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He who begets a scoffer does  so to his sorrow,And the father of a
        fool has no joy.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: A merry heart does good, like medicine,But a broken spirit dries the
        bones.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: A wicked man accepts a bribe behind the backTo pervert the ways of
        justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Wisdom is in the sight of him who has understanding,But the eyes of
        a fool are on the ends of the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: A foolish son is a grief to his father,And bitterness to her who bore
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Also, to punish the righteous is not good,Nor to strike princes for
        their uprightness.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: He who has knowledge spares his words,And a man of understanding is
        of a calm spirit.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Even a fool is counted wise when he holds his peace;When he shuts
        his lips, he  is  considered perceptive.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: A man who isolates himself seeks his own desire;He rages against all
        wise judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: A fool has no delight in understanding,But in expressing his own heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: When the wicked comes, contempt comes also;And with dishonor comes
        reproach.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The words of a man\u2019s mouth are deep waters;The wellspring of
        wisdom is a flowing brook."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: It  is not good to show partiality to the wicked,Or to overthrow the
        righteous in judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A fool\u2019s lips enter into contention,And his mouth calls for
        blows."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "A fool\u2019s mouth is his destruction,And his lips are the snare
        of his soul."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The words of a talebearer are like tasty trifles,And they go down
        into the inmost body.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He who is slothful in his workIs a brother to him who is a great destroyer.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The name of the Lord  is a strong tower;The righteous run to it and
        are safe.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The rich man\u2019s wealth is his strong city,And like a high wall
        in his own esteem."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Before destruction the heart of a man is haughty,And before honor
        is humility.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He who answers a matter before he hears it,It is folly and shame to
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The spirit of a man will sustain him in sickness,But who can bear
        a broken spirit?
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The heart of the prudent acquires knowledge,And the ear of the wise
        seeks knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "A man\u2019s gift makes room for him,And brings him before great
        men."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The first one to plead his cause seems right,Until his neighbor comes
        and examines him.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Casting lots causes contentions to cease,And keeps the mighty apart.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: A brother offended is  harder  to  win than a strong city,And contentions
        are like the bars of a castle.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "A man\u2019s stomach shall be satisfied from the fruit of his mouth;From
        the produce of his lips he shall be filled."
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Death and life are in the power of the tongue,And those who love it
        will eat its fruit.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: He  who finds a wife finds a good thing,And obtains favor from the
        Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The poor man uses entreaties,But the rich answers roughly.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: A man who  has friends must himself be friendly,But there is a friend
        who sticks closer than a brother.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Better is the poor who walks in his integrityThan one  who  is perverse
        in his lips, and is a fool.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Also it is not good for a soul to  be without knowledge,And he sins
        who hastens with his feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: The foolishness of a man twists his way,And his heart frets against
        the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Wealth makes many friends,But the poor is separated from his friend.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A false witness will not go unpunished,And he  who speaks lies will
        not escape.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Many entreat the favor of the nobility,And every man is a friend to
        one who gives gifts.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: All the brothers of the poor hate him;How much more do his friends
        go far from him!He may pursue them  with words, yet they abandon him.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He who gets wisdom loves his own soul;He who keeps understanding will
        find good.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: A false witness will not go unpunished,And he  who speaks lies shall
        perish.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Luxury is not fitting for a fool,Much less for a servant to rule over
        princes.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The discretion of a man makes him slow to anger,And his glory is to
        overlook a transgression.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The king\u2019s wrath is like the roaring of a lion,But his favor
        is  like dew on the grass."
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: A foolish son is the ruin of his father,And the contentions of a wife
        are a continual dripping.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Houses and riches are an inheritance from fathers,But a prudent wife
        is from the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Laziness casts one into a deep sleep,And an idle person will suffer
        hunger.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He who keeps the commandment keeps his soul,But he who is careless
        of his ways will die.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He who has pity on the poor lends to the Lord,And He will pay back
        what he has given.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Chasten your son while there is hope,And do not set your heart on
        his destruction.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: A  man  of great wrath will suffer punishment;For if you rescue him,
        you will have to do it again.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Listen to counsel and receive instruction,That you may be wise in
        your latter days.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "There are many plans in a man\u2019s heart,Nevertheless the Lord\u2019s
        counsel\u2014that will stand."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: What is desired in a man is kindness,And a poor man is better than
        a liar.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The fear of the Lord  leads to life,And he  who  has  it will abide
        in satisfaction;He will not be visited with evil.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: A lazy man buries his hand in the bowl,And will not so much as bring
        it to his mouth again.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Strike a scoffer, and the simple will become wary;Rebuke one who has
        understanding, and he will discern knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He who mistreats his father and chases away his motherIs  a son who
        causes shame and brings reproach.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Cease listening to instruction, my son,And you will stray from the
        words of knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A disreputable witness scorns justice,And the mouth of the wicked
        devours iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Judgments are prepared for scoffers,And beatings for the backs of
        fools.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Wine is a mocker,Strong drink is a brawler,And whoever is led astray
        by it is not wise.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The wrath of a king is like the roaring of a lion;Whoever provokes
        him to anger sins against his own life.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: It  is honorable for a man to stop striving,Since any fool can start
        a quarrel.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The lazy man will not plow because of winter;He will beg during harvest
        and have nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Counsel in the heart of man is  like deep water,But a man of understanding
        will draw it out.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Most men will proclaim each his own goodness,But who can find a faithful
        man?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The righteous man walks in his integrity;His children are blessed
        after him.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: A king who sits on the throne of judgmentScatters all evil with his
        eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Who can say, \u201CI have made my heart clean,I am pure from my sin\u201D?"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Diverse weights and diverse measures,They are both alike, an abomination
        to the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Even a child is known by his deeds,Whether what he does is pure and
        right.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The hearing ear and the seeing eye,The Lord has made them both.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Do not love sleep, lest you come to poverty;Open your eyes, and you
        will be satisfied with bread.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIt  is good for nothing,\u201D cries the buyer;But when he
        has gone his way, then he boasts."
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: There is gold and a multitude of rubies,But the lips of knowledge
        are a precious jewel.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Take the garment of one who is surety for a stranger,And hold it as
        a pledge when  it is for a seductress.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Bread gained by deceit is sweet to a man,But afterward his mouth will
        be filled with gravel.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Plans are established by counsel;By wise counsel wage war.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He who goes about as a talebearer reveals secrets;Therefore do not
        associate with one who flatters with his lips.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Whoever curses his father or his mother,His lamp will be put out in
        deep darkness.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: An inheritance gained hastily at the beginningWill not be blessed
        at the end.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Do not say, \u201CI will recompense evil\u201D;Wait for the Lord,
        and He will save you."
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Diverse weights are an abomination to the Lord,And dishonest scales
        are not good.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "A man\u2019s steps are of the Lord;How then can a man understand
        his own way?"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: It  is a snare for a man to devote rashly something  as holy,And afterward
        to reconsider his vows.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: A wise king sifts out the wicked,And brings the threshing wheel over
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The spirit of a man is the lamp of the Lord,Searching all the inner
        depths of his heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Mercy and truth preserve the king,And by lovingkindness he upholds
        his throne.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: The glory of young men is their strength,And the splendor of old men
        is their gray head.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Blows that hurt cleanse away evil,As do stripes the inner depths of
        the heart.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "The king\u2019s heart is in the hand of the Lord,Like the rivers
        of water;He turns it wherever He wishes."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Every way of a man is right in his own eyes,But the Lord weighs the
        hearts.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: To do righteousness and justiceIs more acceptable to the Lord than
        sacrifice.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: A haughty look, a proud heart,And the plowing of the wicked are sin.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The plans of the diligent lead surely to plenty,But those  of everyone
        who  is hasty, surely to poverty.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Getting treasures by a lying tongueIs the fleeting fantasy of those
        who seek death.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The violence of the wicked will destroy them,Because they refuse to
        do justice.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The way of a guilty man is perverse;But as  for the pure, his work
        is right.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Better to dwell in a corner of a housetop,Than in a house shared with
        a contentious woman.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The soul of the wicked desires evil;His neighbor finds no favor in
        his eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: When the scoffer is punished, the simple is made wise;But when the
        wise is instructed, he receives knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The righteous God wisely considers the house of the wicked,Overthrowing
        the wicked for their wickedness.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Whoever shuts his ears to the cry of the poorWill also cry himself
        and not be heard.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: A gift in secret pacifies anger,And a bribe behind the back, strong
        wrath.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: It  is a joy for the just to do justice,But destruction will  come
        to the workers of iniquity.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: A man who wanders from the way of understandingWill rest in the assembly
        of the dead.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He who loves pleasure will  be a poor man;He who loves wine and oil
        will not be rich.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: The wicked shall  be a ransom for the righteous,And the unfaithful
        for the upright.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Better to dwell in the wilderness,Than with a contentious and angry
        woman.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: There  is desirable treasure,And oil in the dwelling of the wise,But
        a foolish man squanders it.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He who follows righteousness and mercyFinds life, righteousness, and
        honor.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: A wise man scales the city of the mighty,And brings down the trusted
        stronghold.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Whoever guards his mouth and tongueKeeps his soul from troubles.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "A proud and haughty man\u2014 \u201CScoffer\u201D is his name;He
        acts with arrogant pride."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The desire of the lazy man kills him,For his hands refuse to labor.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He covets greedily all day long,But the righteous gives and does not
        spare.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination;How much more when he
        brings it with wicked intent!
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A false witness shall perish,But the man who hears him will speak
        endlessly.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: A wicked man hardens his face,But as  for the upright, he establishes
        his way.
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: There  is no wisdom or understandingOr counsel against the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The horse is prepared for the day of battle,But deliverance is of
        the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: A good name is to be chosen rather than great riches,Loving favor
        rather than silver and gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: The rich and the poor have this in common,The Lord  is the maker of
        them all.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: A prudent man foresees evil and hides himself,But the simple pass
        on and are punished.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: By humility and the fear of the LordAre riches and honor and life.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Thorns and snares are in the way of the perverse;He who guards his
        soul will be far from them.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Train up a child in the way he should go,And when he is old he will
        not depart from it.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The rich rules over the poor,And the borrower is servant to the lender.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He who sows iniquity will reap sorrow,And the rod of his anger will
        fail.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: He who has a generous eye will be blessed,For he gives of his bread
        to the poor.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Cast out the scoffer, and contention will leave;Yes, strife and reproach
        will cease.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: He who loves purity of heartAnd  has grace on his lips,The king will 
        be his friend.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The eyes of the Lord preserve knowledge,But He overthrows the words
        of the faithless.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The lazy man says, \u201CThere  is a lion outside!I shall be slain
        in the streets!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The mouth of an immoral woman is a deep pit;He who is abhorred by
        the Lord will fall there.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Foolishness is bound up in the heart of a child;The rod of correction
        will drive it far from him.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Sayings of the Wise'
      title: Sayings of the Wise
      number: 16
      content: He who oppresses the poor to increase his riches,And he who gives
        to the rich, will surely come to poverty.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Incline your ear and hear the words of the wise,And apply your heart
        to my knowledge;
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For it  is a pleasant thing if you keep them within you;Let them all
        be fixed upon your lips,
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So that your trust may be in the Lord;I have instructed you today,
        even you.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Have I not written to you excellent thingsOf counsels and knowledge,
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: That I may make you know the certainty of the words of truth,That
        you may answer words of truthTo those who send to you?
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Do not rob the poor because he is poor,Nor oppress the afflicted at
        the gate;
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For the Lord will plead their cause,And plunder the soul of those
        who plunder them.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Make no friendship with an angry man,And with a furious man do not
        go,
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Lest you learn his waysAnd set a snare for your soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Do not be one of those who shakes hands in a pledge,One of those who
        is surety for debts;
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: If you have nothing with  which to pay,Why should he take away your
        bed from under you?
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Do not remove the ancient landmarkWhich your fathers have set.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Do you see a man who excels in his work?He will stand before kings;He
        will not stand before unknown men.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: When you sit down to eat with a ruler,Consider carefully what is before
        you;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And put a knife to your throatIf you are a man given to appetite.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Do not desire his delicacies,For they are deceptive food.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Do not overwork to be rich;Because of your own understanding, cease!
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Will you set your eyes on that which is not?For riches certainly make
        themselves wings;They fly away like an eagle toward heaven.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Do not eat the bread of a miser,Nor desire his delicacies;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For as he thinks in his heart, so is he.\u201CEat and drink!\u201D
        he says to you,But his heart is not with you."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The morsel you have eaten, you will vomit up,And waste your pleasant
        words.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Do not speak in the hearing of a fool,For he will despise the wisdom
        of your words.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Do not remove the ancient landmark,Nor enter the fields of the fatherless;
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For their Redeemer is mighty;He will plead their cause against you.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Apply your heart to instruction,And your ears to words of knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Do not withhold correction from a child,For if you beat him with a
        rod, he will not die.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: You shall beat him with a rod,And deliver his soul from hell.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "My son, if your heart is wise,My heart will rejoice\u2014indeed,
        I myself;"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Yes, my inmost being will rejoiceWhen your lips speak right things.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Do not let your heart envy sinners,But be  zealous for the fear of
        the Lord all the day;
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For surely there is a hereafter,And your hope will not be cut off.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Hear, my son, and be wise;And guide your heart in the way.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Do not mix with winebibbers,Or with gluttonous eaters of meat;
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: For the drunkard and the glutton will come to poverty,And drowsiness
        will clothe a  man with rags.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Listen to your father who begot you,And do not despise your mother
        when she is old.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Buy the truth, and do not sell it,Also wisdom and instruction and
        understanding.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The father of the righteous will greatly rejoice,And he who begets
        a wise child will delight in him.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Let your father and your mother be glad,And let her who bore you rejoice.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: My son, give me your heart,And let your eyes observe my ways.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: For a harlot is a deep pit,And a seductress is a narrow well.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: She also lies in wait as for a victim,And increases the unfaithful
        among men.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Who has woe?Who has sorrow?Who has contentions?Who has complaints?Who
        has wounds without cause?Who has redness of eyes?
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Those who linger long at the wine,Those who go in search of mixed
        wine.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Do not look on the wine when it is red,When it sparkles in the cup,When
        it swirls around smoothly;
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: At the last it bites like a serpent,And stings like a viper.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Your eyes will see strange things,And your heart will utter perverse
        things.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Yes, you will be like one who lies down in the midst of the sea,Or
        like one who lies at the top of the mast, saying:'
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThey have struck me, but I was not hurt;They have beaten me,
        but I did not feel it.When shall I awake, that I may seek another drink?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Do not be envious of evil men,Nor desire to be with them;
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: For their heart devises violence,And their lips talk of troublemaking.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Through wisdom a house is built,And by understanding it is established;
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: By knowledge the rooms are filledWith all precious and pleasant riches.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A wise man is strong,Yes, a man of knowledge increases strength;
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: For by wise counsel you will wage your own war,And in a multitude
        of counselors there  is safety.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Wisdom is too lofty for a fool;He does not open his mouth in the gate.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He who plots to do evilWill be called a schemer.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: The devising of foolishness is sin,And the scoffer is an abomination
        to men.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: If you faint in the day of adversity,Your strength is small.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Deliver those  who are drawn toward death,And hold back those stumbling
        to the slaughter.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If you say, \u201CSurely we did not know this,\u201DDoes not He who
        weighs the hearts consider it?He who keeps your soul, does He not know it?And
        will He not render to each man according to his deeds?"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: My son, eat honey because it  is good,And the honeycomb which  is
        sweet to your taste;
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: So shall the knowledge of wisdom be to your soul;If you have found
        it, there is a prospect,And your hope will not be cut off.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Do not lie in wait, O wicked man, against the dwelling of the righteous;Do
        not plunder his resting place;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: For a righteous man may fall seven timesAnd rise again,But the wicked
        shall fall by calamity.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Do not rejoice when your enemy falls,And do not let your heart be
        glad when he stumbles;
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Lest the Lord see it, and it displease Him,And He turn away His wrath
        from him.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Do not fret because of evildoers,Nor be envious of the wicked;
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: For there will be no prospect for the evil man;The lamp of the wicked
        will be put out.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: My son, fear the Lord and the king;Do not associate with those given
        to change;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Further Sayings of the Wise'
      title: Further Sayings of the Wise
      number: 22
      content: For their calamity will rise suddenly,And who knows the ruin those
        two can bring?
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: These things also belong to the wise:It  is not good to show partiality
        in judgment.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He who says to the wicked, \u201CYou are righteous,\u201DHim the
        people will curse;Nations will abhor him."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But those who rebuke the  wicked will have delight,And a good blessing
        will come upon them.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He who gives a right answer kisses the lips.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Prepare your outside work,Make it fit for yourself in the field;And
        afterward build your house.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Do not be a witness against your neighbor without cause,For would
        you deceive with your lips?
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Do not say, \u201CI will do to him just as he has done to me;I will
        render to the man according to his work.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: I went by the field of the lazy man,And by the vineyard of the man
        devoid of understanding;
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: And there it was, all overgrown with thorns;Its surface was covered
        with nettles;Its stone wall was broken down.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When I saw it, I considered it well;I looked on it  and received
        instruction:'
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: A little sleep, a little slumber,A little folding of the hands to
        rest;
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: So shall your poverty come like a prowler,And your need like an armed
        man.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Further Wise Sayings of Solomon'
      title: Further Wise Sayings of Solomon
      number: 1
      content: 'These also are proverbs of Solomon which the men of Hezekiah king
        of Judah copied:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: It  is the glory of God to conceal a matter,But the glory of kings
        is to search out a matter.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: As the heavens for height and the earth for depth,So the heart of
        kings is unsearchable.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Take away the dross from silver,And it will go to the silversmith
        for jewelry.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Take away the wicked from before the king,And his throne will be established
        in righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Do not exalt yourself in the presence of the king,And do not stand
        in the place of the great;
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For it  is better that he say to you,\u201CCome up here,\u201DThan
        that you should be put lower in the presence of the prince,Whom your eyes
        have seen."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Do not go hastily to court;For what will you do in the end,When your
        neighbor has put you to shame?
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Debate your case with your neighbor,And do not disclose the secret
        to another;
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Lest he who hears it expose your shame,And your reputation be ruined.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: A word fitly spoken is  like apples of goldIn settings of silver.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Like an earring of gold and an ornament of fine goldIs a wise rebuker
        to an obedient ear.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Like the cold of snow in time of harvestIs a faithful messenger to
        those who send him,For he refreshes the soul of his masters.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Whoever falsely boasts of givingIs  like  clouds and wind without
        rain.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: By long forbearance a ruler is persuaded,And a gentle tongue breaks
        a bone.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Have you found honey?Eat only as much as you need,Lest you be filled
        with it and vomit.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Seldom set foot in your neighbor\u2019s house,Lest he become weary
        of you and hate you."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: A man who bears false witness against his neighborIs  like a club,
        a sword, and a sharp arrow.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of troubleIs  like a bad tooth
        and a foot out of joint.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Like one who takes away a garment in cold weather,And  like vinegar
        on soda,Is one who sings songs to a heavy heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: If your enemy is hungry, give him bread to eat;And if he is thirsty,
        give him water to drink;
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For so you will heap coals of fire on his head,And the Lord will reward
        you.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: The north wind brings forth rain,And a backbiting tongue an angry
        countenance.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: It  is better to dwell in a corner of a housetop,Than in a house shared
        with a contentious woman.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: As cold water to a weary soul,So is  good news from a far country.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: A righteous man who falters before the wickedIs  like a murky spring
        and a polluted well.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "It  is not good to eat much honey;So to seek one\u2019s own glory
        is  not glory."
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Whoever has no rule over his own spiritIs  like a city broken down,
        without walls.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: As snow in summer and rain in harvest,So honor is not fitting for
        a fool.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Like a flitting sparrow, like a flying swallow,So a curse without
        cause shall not alight.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A whip for the horse,A bridle for the donkey,And a rod for the fool\u2019s
        back."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Do not answer a fool according to his folly,Lest you also be like
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Answer a fool according to his folly,Lest he be wise in his own eyes.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: He who sends a message by the hand of a foolCuts off his  own feet
        and drinks violence.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Like the legs of the lame that hang limpIs a proverb in the mouth
        of fools.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Like one who binds a stone in a slingIs he who gives honor to a fool.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Like a thorn that goes into the hand of a drunkardIs a proverb in
        the mouth of fools.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The great God who formed everythingGives the fool his hire and the
        transgressor his wages.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: As a dog returns to his own vomit,So a fool repeats his folly.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Do you see a man wise in his own eyes?There  is more hope for a fool
        than for him.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The lazy man says, \u201CThere  is a lion in the road!A fierce lion
        is in the streets!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: As a door turns on its hinges,So does the lazy man on his bed.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The lazy man buries his hand in the bowl;It wearies him to bring it
        back to his mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: The lazy man  is wiser in his own eyesThan seven men who can answer
        sensibly.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: He who passes by and meddles in a quarrel not his ownIs  like one
        who takes a dog by the ears.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Like a madman who throws firebrands, arrows, and death,
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Is the man who deceives his neighbor,And says, \u201CI was only joking!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Where there  is no wood, the fire goes out;And where there  is no
        talebearer, strife ceases.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: As charcoal is to burning coals, and wood to fire,So is a contentious
        man to kindle strife.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The words of a talebearer are like tasty trifles,And they go down
        into the inmost body.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Fervent lips with a wicked heartAre  like earthenware covered with
        silver dross.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: He who hates, disguises it with his lips,And lays up deceit within
        himself;
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: When he speaks kindly, do not believe him,For there  are seven abominations
        in his heart;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Though  his hatred is covered by deceit,His wickedness will be revealed
        before the assembly.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Whoever digs a pit will fall into it,And he who rolls a stone will
        have it roll back on him.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A lying tongue hates those  who  are crushed by it,And a flattering
        mouth works ruin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Do not boast about tomorrow,For you do not know what a day may bring
        forth.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Let another man praise you, and not your own mouth;A stranger, and
        not your own lips.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A stone is heavy and sand is weighty,But a fool\u2019s wrath is heavier
        than both of them."
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Wrath is cruel and anger a torrent,But who is able to stand before
        jealousy?
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Open rebuke is betterThan love carefully concealed.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Faithful are the wounds of a friend,But the kisses of an enemy are 
        deceitful.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: A satisfied soul loathes the honeycomb,But to a hungry soul every
        bitter thing is sweet.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Like a bird that wanders from its nestIs a man who wanders from his
        place.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Ointment and perfume delight the heart,And the sweetness of a man\u2019s
        friend gives  delight by hearty counsel."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Do not forsake your own friend or your father\u2019s friend,Nor go
        to your brother\u2019s house in the day of your calamity;Better is a neighbor
        nearby than a brother far away."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: My son, be wise, and make my heart glad,That I may answer him who
        reproaches me.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: A prudent man foresees evil and hides himself;The simple pass on and
        are punished.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Take the garment of him who is surety for a stranger,And hold it in
        pledge when he is surety for a seductress.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: He who blesses his friend with a loud voice, rising early in the morning,It
        will be counted a curse to him.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: A continual dripping on a very rainy dayAnd a contentious woman are
        alike;
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Whoever restrains her restrains the wind,And grasps oil with his right
        hand.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: As iron sharpens iron,So a man sharpens the countenance of his friend.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Whoever keeps the fig tree will eat its fruit;So he who waits on his
        master will be honored.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "As in water face reflects face,So a man\u2019s heart reveals the
        man."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Hell and Destruction are never full;So the eyes of man are never satisfied.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: The refining pot is for silver and the furnace for gold,And a man
        is  valued by what others say of him.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Though you grind a fool in a mortar with a pestle along with crushed
        grain,Yet his foolishness will not depart from him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Be diligent to know the state of your flocks,And attend to your herds;
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: For riches are not forever,Nor does a crown endure to all generations.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: When the hay is removed, and the tender grass shows itself,And the
        herbs of the mountains are gathered in,
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The lambs will  provide your clothing,And the goats the price of a
        field;
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "You  shall  have enough goats\u2019 milk for your food,For the food
        of your household,And the nourishment of your maidservants."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: The wicked flee when no one pursues,But the righteous are bold as
        a lion.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Because of the transgression of a land, many are its princes;But by
        a man of understanding and knowledgeRight will be prolonged.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: A poor man who oppresses the poorIs  like a driving rain which leaves
        no food.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Those who forsake the law praise the wicked,But such as keep the law
        contend with them.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Evil men do not understand justice,But those who seek the Lord understand
        all.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Better is the poor who walks in his integrityThan one perverse in 
        his ways, though he be rich.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Whoever keeps the law is a discerning son,But a companion of gluttons
        shames his father.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: One who increases his possessions by usury and extortionGathers it
        for him who will pity the poor.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: One who turns away his ear from hearing the law,Even his prayer is
        an abomination.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Whoever causes the upright to go astray in an evil way,He himself
        will fall into his own pit;But the blameless will inherit good.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The rich man is wise in his own eyes,But the poor who has understanding
        searches him out.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: When the righteous rejoice, there  is great glory;But when the wicked
        arise, men hide themselves.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He who covers his sins will not prosper,But whoever confesses and
        forsakes them will have mercy.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Happy is the man who is always reverent,But he who hardens his heart
        will fall into calamity.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Like a roaring lion and a charging bearIs a wicked ruler over poor
        people.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: A ruler who lacks understanding is a great oppressor,But he who hates
        covetousness will prolong his days.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: A man burdened with bloodshed will flee into a pit;Let no one help
        him.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Whoever walks blamelessly will be saved,But he  who  is perverse in 
        his ways will suddenly fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: He who tills his land will have plenty of bread,But he who follows
        frivolity will have poverty enough!
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: A faithful man will abound with blessings,But he who hastens to be
        rich will not go unpunished.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: To show partiality is not good,Because for a piece of bread a man
        will transgress.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: A man with an evil eye hastens after riches,And does not consider
        that poverty will come upon him.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He who rebukes a man will find more favor afterwardThan he who flatters
        with the tongue.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Whoever robs his father or his mother,And says, \u201CIt  is no transgression,\u201DThe
        same is companion to a destroyer."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: He who is of a proud heart stirs up strife,But he who trusts in the
        Lord will be prospered.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: He who trusts in his own heart is a fool,But whoever walks wisely
        will be delivered.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: He who gives to the poor will not lack,But he who hides his eyes will
        have many curses.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: When the wicked arise, men hide themselves;But when they perish, the
        righteous increase.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: He who is often rebuked, and hardens his neck,Will suddenly be destroyed,
        and that without remedy.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice;But when a
        wicked man rules, the people groan.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Whoever loves wisdom makes his father rejoice,But a companion of harlots
        wastes his wealth.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: The king establishes the land by justice,But he who receives bribes
        overthrows it.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: A man who flatters his neighborSpreads a net for his feet.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: By transgression an evil man is snared,But the righteous sings and
        rejoices.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: The righteous considers the cause of the poor,But the wicked does
        not understand such knowledge.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Scoffers set a city aflame,But wise men turn away wrath.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: If a wise man contends with a foolish man,Whether the  fool rages
        or laughs, there  is no peace.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: The bloodthirsty hate the blameless,But the upright seek his well-being.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: A fool vents all his feelings,But a wise man holds them back.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: If a ruler pays attention to lies,All his servants become wicked.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: The poor man and the oppressor have this in common:The Lord gives
        light to the eyes of both.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The king who judges the poor with truth,His throne will be established
        forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The rod and rebuke give wisdom,But a child left to  himself brings
        shame to his mother.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: When the wicked are multiplied, transgression increases;But the righteous
        will see their fall.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Correct your son, and he will give you rest;Yes, he will give delight
        to your soul.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Where there  is no revelation, the people cast off restraint;But happy
        is he who keeps the law.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: A servant will not be corrected by mere words;For though he understands,
        he will not respond.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Do you see a man hasty in his words?There  is more hope for a fool
        than for him.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He who pampers his servant from childhoodWill have him as a son in
        the end.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: An angry man stirs up strife,And a furious man abounds in transgression.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "A man\u2019s pride will bring him low,But the humble in spirit will
        retain honor."
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Whoever is a partner with a thief hates his own life;He swears to
        tell the truth, but reveals nothing.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The fear of man brings a snare,But whoever trusts in the Lord shall
        be safe.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Many seek the ruler\u2019s favor,But justice for man comes from the
        Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: An unjust man is an abomination to the righteous,And he  who  is upright
        in the way is an abomination to the wicked.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wisdom of Agur'
      title: The Wisdom of Agur
      number: 1
      content: "The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, his utterance. This man declared
        to Ithiel\u2014to Ithiel and Ucal:"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Surely I am more stupid than any man,And do not have the understanding
        of a man.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: I neither learned wisdomNor have knowledge of the Holy One.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who has ascended into heaven, or descended?Who has gathered the wind
        in His fists?Who has bound the waters in a garment?Who has established all
        the ends of the earth?What is His name, and what is His Son\u2019s name,If
        you know?"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Every word of God is pure;He is a shield to those who put their trust
        in Him.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Do not add to His words,Lest He rebuke you, and you be found a liar.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Two things I request of You(Deprive me not before I die):'
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Remove falsehood and lies far from me;Give me neither poverty nor
        riches\u2014Feed me with the food allotted to me;"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Lest I be full and deny You,And say, \u201CWho is the Lord?\u201DOr
        lest I be poor and steal,And profane the name of my God."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Do not malign a servant to his master,Lest he curse you, and you be
        found guilty.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: There  is a generation that curses its father,And does not bless its
        mother.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: There  is a generation that  is pure in its own eyes,Yet is not washed
        from its filthiness.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "There  is a generation\u2014oh, how lofty are their eyes!And their
        eyelids are lifted up."
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: There  is a generation whose teeth are  like swords,And whose fangs
        are  like knives,To devour the poor from off the earth,And the needy from
        among men.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The leech has two daughters\u2014Give and Give!There are three things 
        that are never satisfied,Four never say, \u201CEnough!\u201D:"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The grave,The barren womb,The earth that is not satisfied with water\u2014And
        the fire never says, \u201CEnough!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The eye that mocks his father,And scorns obedience to his mother,The
        ravens of the valley will pick it out,And the young eagles will eat it.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There are three things  which are too wonderful for me,Yes, four
        which I do not understand:'
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: The way of an eagle in the air,The way of a serpent on a rock,The
        way of a ship in the midst of the sea,And the way of a man with a virgin.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This is the way of an adulterous woman:She eats and wipes her mouth,And
        says, \u201CI have done no wickedness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For three things the earth is perturbed,Yes, for four it cannot bear
        up:'
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: For a servant when he reigns,A fool when he is filled with food,
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: A hateful woman when she is married,And a maidservant who succeeds
        her mistress.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'There are four things  which are little on the earth,But they are
        exceedingly wise:'
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The ants are a people not strong,Yet they prepare their food in the
        summer;
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: The rock badgers are a feeble folk,Yet they make their homes in the
        crags;
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The locusts have no king,Yet they all advance in ranks;
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "The spider skillfully grasps with its hands,And it is in kings\u2019
        palaces."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'There are three things  which are majestic in pace,Yes, four which
        are stately in walk:'
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: A lion, which  is mighty among beastsAnd does not turn away from any;
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: A greyhound,A male goat also,And a king whose troops are with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: If you have been foolish in exalting yourself,Or if you have devised
        evil, put  your hand on your mouth.
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For as the churning of milk produces butter,And wringing the nose
        produces blood,So the forcing of wrath produces strife.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Words of King Lemuel\u2019s Mother"
      title: "The Words of King Lemuel\u2019s Mother"
      number: 1
      content: 'The words of King Lemuel, the utterance which his mother taught him:'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: What, my son?And what, son of my womb?And what, son of my vows?
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Do not give your strength to women,Nor your ways to that which destroys
        kings.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: It  is not for kings, O Lemuel,It  is not for kings to drink wine,Nor
        for princes intoxicating drink;
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Lest they drink and forget the law,And pervert the justice of all
        the afflicted.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Give strong drink to him who is perishing,And wine to those who are
        bitter of heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Let him drink and forget his poverty,And remember his misery no more.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Open your mouth for the speechless,In the cause of all who  are appointed
        to die.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Virtuous Wife'
      title: The Virtuous Wife
      number: 9
      content: Open your mouth, judge righteously,And plead the cause of the poor
        and needy.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Who can find a virtuous wife?For her worth is far above rubies.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The heart of her husband safely trusts her;So he will have no lack
        of gain.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: She does him good and not evilAll the days of her life.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: She seeks wool and flax,And willingly works with her hands.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: She is like the merchant ships,She brings her food from afar.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: She also rises while it is yet night,And provides food for her household,And
        a portion for her maidservants.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: She considers a field and buys it;From her profits she plants a vineyard.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: She girds herself with strength,And strengthens her arms.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: She perceives that her merchandise is good,And her lamp does not go
        out by night.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: She stretches out her hands to the distaff,And her hand holds the
        spindle.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: She extends her hand to the poor,Yes, she reaches out her hands to
        the needy.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: She is not afraid of snow for her household,For all her household
        is clothed with scarlet.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: She makes tapestry for herself;Her clothing is fine linen and purple.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Her husband is known in the gates,When he sits among the elders of
        the land.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: She makes linen garments and sells them,And supplies sashes for the
        merchants.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Strength and honor are her clothing;She shall rejoice in time to come.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: She opens her mouth with wisdom,And on her tongue is the law of kindness.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: She watches over the ways of her household,And does not eat the bread
        of idleness.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Her children rise up and call her blessed;Her husband also, and he
        praises her:'
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CMany daughters have done well,But you excel them all.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Charm is deceitful and beauty is passing,But a woman who fears the
        Lord, she shall be praised.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Give her of the fruit of her hands,And let her own works praise her
        in the gates.
      comments: []
